Generate files from gensort using the below command
    ./gensort -a 1000 input.txt
The above command generates 1000 lines of tuples of 3 columns,each having a size of 100 Bytes
and stores it under the name input.txt

Command to run the code
    1) javac sort.java
    2) java sort input.txt output.txt metadata.txt MainMemorySize(MB)​ sortOrder(asc or desc) column0 column1 . . .

General Format of arguments for command line is
    java sort​ input.txt output.txt metadata.txt MainMemorySize(MB)​ sortOrder(asc or desc) column0 column1 . . .

Examples -
    java sort​ input.txt output.txt metadata.txt 50​ asc c0 c1
    java sort​ input.txt output.txt​ metadata.txt 100​ desc​ c0

Using Valsort to validate the answer
    The commands "./valsort output.txt" gives the output as whether
    or not the output file is in sorted order or not
